tourBios.carHigh:
2015: Finished T13 at the Canada Qualifying Tournament, with rounds of 70-72-72-71.

2012: Made the cut in all six events he played, including a season-best T6 at The Great Waterway Classic. 2011: Made three cuts in five starts, with his best finish a T27 at the TOUR Championship. 2009: Finished a season-best T12 at the Seaforth Country Classic. 2008: Finished T6 at the Corona Mazatlan Mexican PGA Championship. 2005: Had six top-10 finishes. A second-place finish on the Order of Merit gave him an exemption into the second stage of the PGA TOUR Qualifying School. 1997: Made nine consecutive cuts on the Web.com Tour. 1996: Won the Panama Open and reached the final stage of the PGA TOUR Qualifying School. 1995: Had three top 10s on the Web.com Tour. 1993: Made 15 of 29 cuts on the PGA TOUR. 1992: Won the Web.com Tour's Boise Open with an 11-under 202.
tourBios.personal: Favorite course he's played is Pebble Beach and wants to play Augusta National...Dream foursome would include his dad, brother and Ben Hogan...Favorite pro sports' team is the Dallas Cowboys...Played the final round of the Sarazen World Open with Jack Nicklaus.
tourBios.otherInfo: Has had 30 career victories as a pro.

dyn.dynResults: He has finished 6th on the Mackenzie Tour-PGA T 2 times.
dyn.dynStats: He ranks T17th in Par 3 Birdie or Better Leaders on the PGA TOUR Canada.
